Exception propagation
Exception propagation in Java means that when a method throws an exception and does not handle it (using try-catch), the exception is automatically passed to the calling method. 
This continues up the call stack until it is caught or reaches the JVM.
Propagation happens only for unchecked exceptions (like ArithmeticException) by default.
